The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 3: Cadila Healthcare will allot 6.28 crore bonus shares in the ratio of 1:1 to its shareholders. The AGM held last month authorised the board to issue 6,28,06,854 bonus shares of Rs 5 each, where one share would be allotted for every one held. The scrip closed at Rs 559.90 on the BSE today, up 1.44 per cent from its last close.

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: Bharti Airtel today announced a $100-million deal with IBM to deliver a suit of new product services and applications under a single delivery platform. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 3: There is no change in Intels plan to set up a manufacturing unit in India and it is awaiting the governments policy on setting up of such IT facilities, company managing director (South Asia) Ramamurthy Sivakumar said.

 Mumbai, Aug. 3: Bayer Diagnostics India Ltd will seek shareholders approval for the sale of its diabetes care business to Bayer Material Science Pvt Ltd, a Bayer group company for Rs 25.74 crore.

 New Delhi, Aug. 3: Iran today refused to lower the price of gas it wants to sell to India and Pakistan through a tri-nation pipeline, but agreed to form an expert committee with members from the three countries to discuss the issue.




